nodes.name: Reginald Cattermole
nodes.birth: Sun in Libra, moon in Virgo
nodes.label: Reginald Cattermole

nodes.name: Neville Longbottom
nodes.Note: This wand was nice for Charm work.
nodes.label: Neville Longbottom

nodes.name: Harry Potter
nodes.Note: Brother to Voldemort's wand — the core tail feathers are both from Fawkes; broken in December 1997 while fleeing from Godric's Hollow;[22] repaired with the Elder Wand in May 1998.
nodes.label: Harry Potter

nodes.name: Ronald Weasley
nodes.Note: Purchased with his father's winnings from a Daily Prophet draw. Taken from him by Snatchers and replaced with Peter Pettigrew's wand.
nodes.label: Ronald Weasley

nodes.name: Hermione Granger
nodes.Note: This wand was confiscated when the trio was captured by Snatchers in 1998.
nodes.label: Hermione Granger

nodes.name: Albus Dumbledore
nodes.Note: The Elder Wand, one of the Deathly Hallows. Also known as the Deathstick and the Wand of Destiny.
nodes.label: Albus Dumbledore

nodes.name: Remus Lupin
nodes.Note: Cypress wands are said to be well-matched to wizards who are self-sacrificing and willing to die a heroic death. Lupin spent the majority of his life alone to save others from having to deal with the consequences of his affliction, and died defending Hogwarts castle in the Battle of Hogwarts.
nodes.label: Remus Lupin

nodes.name: Quirinus Quirrell
nodes.Note: This wand was nice for Charm work.
nodes.label: Quirinus Quirrell

nodes.name: Minerva McGonagall
nodes.Note: This wand was most likely purchased from Ollivanders in 1947 when she was eleven almost twelve.
nodes.label: Minerva McGonagall

nodes.name: Sybill Trelawney
nodes.birth: 9 March, prior to 1963, Great Britain or Ireland
nodes.Note: This wand bears a resemblance to Sirius Black's wand, though there are slight differences. They both have a square-like handle and have magical runes depicted on the wand, but Trelawney's wand has a darker colour and has a swirly shape from the handle to the tip.
nodes.label: Sybill Trelawney

nodes.name: Dolores Umbridge
nodes.Note: This wand is described as 'unusually short;' broken by a centaur's hoof in June 1996 in the Forbidden Forest
nodes.label: Dolores Umbridge

nodes.name: Lucius Malfoy
nodes.Note: This wand was kept in a snake-headed walking stick that Lucius carried; 'borrowed' by Lord Voldemort and destroyed by Harry Potter's wand during the Battle of the Seven Potters in 1997.
nodes.label: Lucius Malfoy

nodes.name: Bellatrix Lestrange
nodes.Note: This wand is described as 'unyielding;' passed into the possession of Hermione Granger after the Skirmish at Malfoy Manor in 1998.
nodes.label: Bellatrix Lestrange

nodes.name: Peter Pettigrew
nodes.Note: This wand may have been one of the last wands Mr Ollivander sold before he disappeared in 1996. This was Peter Pettigrew's wand. During the Skirmish at Malfoy Manor, Ron took this wand from Pettigrew and used from then on, as his own wand was taken by Snatchers.
nodes.label: Peter Pettigrew

nodes.name: James Potter
nodes.Note: This wand was excellent for transfiguration
nodes.label: James Potter

nodes.name: Charlie Weasley
nodes.Note: Ron's brother Charlie's old wand; severely damaged in September 1992 after a run-in with the Whomping Willow.
nodes.label: Charlie Weasley

nodes.name: Bathilda Bagshot
nodes.death: Pre 24 December, 1997 (aged about 124), Godric's Hollow, West Country, England, Great Britain
nodes.label: Bathilda Bagshot

nodes.name: Fleur Delacour
nodes.Note: In this wand the core is a hair from Fleur's grandmother, who was a Veela.
nodes.label: Fleur Delacour

nodes.name: Ginny Weasley
nodes.Note: A yew wand is suited for a person who is a fierce protector of others.[3] Protectiveness is an espect of Ginny's personality. She has frequently defended Harry Potter against others.
nodes.label: Ginny Weasley

nodes.name: Bartemius Crouch Junior
nodes.death: c.1995-1996(aged 33 - 34) (received the Dementor's Kiss on 24 June, 1995)
nodes.label: Bartemius Crouch Junior
